    <bioghist>Son of Edward Nicolaus Heinrich and Elizabeth Louise Bode, Bode was born in Howell, Michigan, October 26, 1872. He spent his life and career in Howell where he worked as a tailor's apprentice, post office clerk, stenographer, bookkeeper, paymaster, editor, auditor and controller of the Citizens Mutual Auto Insurance Company. Emil retired from the insurance company in 1944.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Letters from life-long friend, Harlow S. Person, economist, mainly in the period before 1900. Harlowe discusses current events, friendships, romantic relationships, matters pertaining to Person's father's tenure as a circuit judge and his experiences as a student (A.M., 1900; Ph.D., 1903) at the University of Michigan, 1896-1902.</scopecontent>
